	<Title>
		Recipe: Halibut with tomato basil salsa
	</Title>
	<Abstract />
	<ServingInfo Label="Serves">
		4
	</ServingInfo>
	<DietitianTip Label="Dietitian&apos;s tip">
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dietitian&apos;s tip:&lt;/strong&gt; Halibut &amp;mdash; in addition to cod, flounder and perch &amp;mdash; is a lean fish, having less than 2.5 percent fat by weight. For a variation to this recipe, grill the halibut and spoon the tomato basil salsa over each fillet to serve.&lt;/p&gt;
	</DietitianTip>
	<Directions Label="Directions">
		&lt;p&gt;Preheat the oven to 350 F. Lightly coat a 9-by-13-inch baking pan with cooking spray.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In a small bowl, combine the tomato, basil, oregano and garlic. Add the olive oil and mix well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Arrange the halibut fillets in the baking pan. Spoon the tomato mixture over the fish. Place in the oven and bake until the fish is opaque throughout when tested with the tip of a knife, about 10 to 15 minutes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Transfer to individual plates and serve immediately.&lt;/p&gt;
	</Directions>
	<Ingredients Label="Ingredients">
		&lt;p&gt;2 tomatoes, diced&lt;br /&gt;
2 tablespoons fresh basil, chopped&lt;br /&gt;
1 teaspoon fresh oregano, chopped&lt;br /&gt;
1 tablespoon minced garlic&lt;br /&gt;
2 teaspoons extra-virgin olive oil&lt;br /&gt;
4 halibut fillets, each 4 ounces&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
	</Ingredients>
